<property name="userLevelDocumentation" class="ptolemy.kernel.util.ConfigurableAttribute"><configure><p>The Round actor rounds a number using a specified rounding function. The actor reads a number of type double (e.g., 102.87),  and outputs the rounded integer.</p>

<p>The actor can use one of four rounding functions:</p>
<ul>
<li>ceil: Round towards positive infinity.</li> 
<li>floor: Round towards negative infinity. </li> 
<li> round: (the default) Round towards nearest integer. </li> 
<li>truncate: Round towards zero.</li> 
</ul>
</configure></property>
